Git


Workflow




git co master


git pull (see if others have made changes in the meantime)


git co -b feature_branch


work work work work work work


git add .


git commit


git push origin feature_branch (to share your work with the team on github)




When you are done with work




git co master


git pull


git co feature_branch


git merge master (resolve merge conflicts, if any)


git co master


git merge --no-ff feature_branch


git push


git branch -d feature_branch (delete the feature branch)

Glossary


During our journey of learning how to build a full-stack Django project,
we will learn many new technical terms. We will try to keep track of them
in this glossary.

Checkout


Commit
